+### 3.4. Narrative Generation (Ollama)
+
+The simulation engine calls a local LLM to produce in-world narrative text wherever human-readable output is needed: event descriptions, turn summary commit messages, hero flavour text, and faction proclamations.
+
+**Narrative call sites:**
+
+| Call site | Input | Output |
+|---|---|---|
+| Turn event descriptions | Event type + affected entities + outcome delta | One-sentence in-world narrative |
+| CI commit message | Full turn summary (events list) | Chronicle-style commit message |
+| Hero trait mutation | Old traits + triggering action | Flavour line explaining the change |
+| Faction proclamation | Faction state + policy change | In-world edict text |
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+```python
+import httpx
+
+NARRATIVE_SYSTEM_PROMPT = (
+    "You write darkly humorous in-world narrative for a bureaucratic fantasy civilization game. "
+    "Be concise (one sentence unless told otherwise). Never break the fourth wall."
+)
+
+def generate_narrative(prompt: str, model: str = "llama3.2") -> str:
+    response = httpx.post("http://localhost:11434/api/chat", json={
+        "model": model,
+        "options": {"temperature": 0.7},
+        "messages": [
+            {"role": "system", "content": NARRATIVE_SYSTEM_PROMPT},
+            {"role": "user", "content": prompt},
+        ]
+    })
+    return response.json()["message"]["content"].strip()
+```
+
+**Fallback:** if Ollama is unreachable (e.g. GitHub Actions CI), the engine falls back to pre-written JSON template strings. All narrative call sites accept an optional `narrative: str` override so CI can inject the template output directly.
 
