+**LLM-driven AI players (Ollama):**
+
+AI-controlled factions can be driven by a locally-run LLM via [Ollama](https://ollama.com) instead of (or alongside) the deterministic rule-based AI. Each AI faction receives a system prompt encoding its personality and doctrine, and is asked to produce orders JSON for the current turn.
+
+```python
+import httpx
+
+def get_ai_orders(faction: str, world_state: dict) -> dict:
+    response = httpx.post("http://localhost:11434/api/chat", json={
+        "model": "llama3.2",
+        "format": "json",
+        "messages": [
+            {"role": "system", "content": f"You are the AI ruler of {faction}. Respond only with valid orders JSON."},
+            {"role": "user", "content": f"Current world state: {world_state}\n\nSubmit your orders."}
+        ]
+    })
+    return response.json()
+```
+
+Implementation notes:
+- Output is validated against `TurnOrders` schema before being passed to `resolve_turn` — LLM output is untrusted
+- Set `"options": {"temperature": 0}` for reproducible/deterministic AI behaviour; raise temperature for chaotic factions
+- 7B-class models (llama3.2, Mistral) run on a laptop and produce adequate strategic reasoning
+- Ollama must be running locally; the CI pipeline on GitHub Actions will skip LLM orders and fall back to rule-based AI if Ollama is unreachable
+
